/* #### Neccessary knowledge to work on style #### */
/*

Style is defined by element, and responsive rules are defined per element.
First, global properties, then, responsive rules, from biggest screen to smallers.
The content of pages is 60% of the sceen width on computers screen and 80% on tablets / phones

Responsive mode is calculated by screen width :

[900px;+infinity[ => Computers version
[650; 900px[ => Tablet version
[0; 649] => Phones version

If a property must be modified for only one/two screen size, we can just keep the normal in global properties, then overwrite it for the target screen
Just make it simple and try to avoid repetitions if possible

Good luck
*/

